---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About SaaSStatsHub — the #1 source for SaaS industry statistics, market size data, growth trends, and adoption rates across CRM, marketing, e-commerce, security, and more.">
  <div class="max-w-[740px] mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About SaaSStatsHub</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-text">SaaSStatsHub</strong> is the #1 source for SaaS statistics, market data, and industry trends in 2026. We provide comprehensive, up-to-date, and always-cited statistics covering the entire SaaS ecosystem — from market size and revenue growth to enterprise adoption rates, pricing benchmarks, and regional insights across 100+ articles and 8 major categories.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        We believe that reliable SaaS industry data should be accessible to everyone. Whether you're a founder building a business case, an analyst writing a market research report, a marketer creating data-driven content, or an investor evaluating SaaS companies, SaaSStatsHub gives you the statistics you need — with original sources you can cite and trust.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">What Makes Us Different</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong class="text-text">Always Cited</strong> — Every statistic links back to its original source (Gartner, Statista, McKinsey, company reports). No phantom numbers.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text">Always Current</strong> — We update our SaaS statistics regularly to reflect the latest 2026 data from quarterly earnings, industry reports, and market research.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text">Comprehensive Coverage</strong> — From SaaS market size ($232B in 2026) to individual platform statistics (Salesforce, HubSpot, Shopify, Zoom), we cover every angle.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-text">Free & Accessible</strong> — All 100+ statistical articles are freely accessible. No paywalls, no subscriptions required.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">How We Work</h2>
      <p>
        Each article starts with source research, not keyword stuffing. We collect public filings,
        vendor documentation, earnings releases, market research summaries, and primary-source
        product data where available. The editorial pass then turns those inputs into plain-English
        takeaways, comparison tables, and context about what the numbers mean for SaaS operators,
        buyers, analysts, and founders.
      </p>
      <p>
        When a number changes, we prefer updating the original page instead of publishing duplicate
        versions. If you spot a stale figure or a weak citation, send us the URL and the data point;
        corrections are reviewed manually before publication.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Coverage Areas</h2>
      <p>We publish in-depth statistics across all major SaaS and technology categories:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li><a href="/categories/crm/" class="text-primary hover:underline">CRM Statistics</a> — Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho, Pipedrive, Microsoft Dynamics 365 market share & revenue</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/marketing/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Marketing Statistics</a> — SEO, PPC, email marketing, social media, content marketing & automation data</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/ecommerce/" class="text-primary hover:underline">E-commerce Statistics</a> — Shopify, WooCommerce, Amazon FBA, Stripe, BigCommerce & online retail trends</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/project-management/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Project Management Statistics</a> — Asana, Jira, Monday.com, Trello, ClickUp, DevOps & Scrum data</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/hr/" class="text-primary hover:underline">HR & Payroll Statistics</a> — Employee engagement, talent acquisition, compensation, benefits & HR technology</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/analytics/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Analytics & SaaS Market Statistics</a> — Cloud computing, big data, AI, business intelligence, SaaS market size & growth</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/security/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Cybersecurity Statistics</a> — Ransomware, data privacy, cloud security, endpoint protection & cyber insurance</li>
        <li><a href="/categories/communication/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Communication Statistics</a> — Zoom, Slack, Microsoft Teams, UCaaS, CPaaS & video conferencing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Key Statistics We Track</h2>
      <p>Our data coverage includes but is not limited to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Global SaaS market size and CAGR growth projections (2024–2030)</li>
        <li>Individual SaaS company revenue, market share, and user counts</li>
        <li>Enterprise vs SMB adoption rates by category</li>
        <li>Regional market data (North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific)</li>
        <li>Pricing trends, churn rates, and customer acquisition costs</li>
        <li>AI and automation adoption in SaaS platforms</li>
        <li>Cybersecurity spending, breach costs, and threat statistics</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Have a question, correction, or suggestion? We'd love to hear from you.
        Reach out at <a href="mailto:sangaypopo@gmail.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">sangaypopo@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
